"Arachnospila trivialis: iso. Day: 1988","212","","Steven Falk","","Suspect some of the BWARS records (esp females) are misidentifications of A. anceps. I don’t see trivialis very often.","0","Y"
"Arachnospila wesmaeli: iso. Day: 1988","212","NT?","Steven Falk","","As per trivialis, many records likely to be misidentified females of A. anceps or A. trivialis as these are very difficult species to identify without comparative material. Most of the Oxford University Museum wesmaeli specimens recently proved to be erroneous. I reckon it now largely confined to western dunes (especially in Wales).","0","Y"
