"Chrysis fulgida: iso. Morgan: 1984","212","NT or VU","Steven Falk","","One of the largest and most easily recognised chrysidids with well-understood ecology. Clearly rare with highly fragmented populations, and seemingly much scarcer than host (Symmorphus crasicornis). No evidence of increase anywhere. Hard to find now. Vulnerable to Aspen clearance in woods (Aspen often treated as a tree weed). Scarce but more stable on the few Welsh dunes where it occurs in association with Creeping Willow-rich dune slacks but scarcer on these dunes than Coelioxys mandibularis (which you've given EN status).","1","Undergraded?"
