"Chrysis 'pseudobrevitarsis'","212","CR","Steven Falk","","Not sure if pseudobrevitarsis is the name still given to the large Chrysis that attacks Ancistrocerus antilope. I seem to be the last person to record it (1989, alongside its host). It is not officially Extinct yet, and the host has only one record since 1989. It is one of the easier 'ignita'group spcies to identify. I believe it is Critically Rare if not extinct.","0",""
