"Chrysura hirsuta: iso. Paukkunen et al: 2015","212","NT or VU","Steven Falk","","Readily identified species in some well-recorded parts of Scotland (notably Cairngorms) so no justification for DD. Seemingly now largely confined to the older pine woods of the Cairngorms where it is dependent on fate of its host bee Osmia uncinata, which I reckon is struggling (due to lack of Bird's-foot Trefoil at many of its sites - see Osmia uncinata entry). ","1","Disagree"
"Cleptes nitidulus: iso. Morgan: 1984","212","NT?","Steven Falk","","Very scarce with fragmented populations. Map suggests significent UK decline. Rarely seen these days though Cleptes species are elusive and probably need targeted recording.","1","Undergraded?"
"Cleptes semiauratus: iso. Morgan: 1984","212","NT?","Steven Falk","","Not sure why NE? A scarce species. Map shows significant UK decline. I've not seen one for years.","1","Undergraded?"
