"Hylaeus incongruus: iso. Straka & Bogusch: 2011","212","NT?","Steven Falk","","Narrative states ""Very hard to ID. Extreme identification difficulties. Name change was direct, not a split"" This is incorrect. identification using Falk (2015) and Else & Edwards (2018) is reasonably straightforward, and nomenclature changes should not have affected the accumulation of records for this species. So no obvious justification for DD. Data shows it is a very scarce species of southern England but being a small bee there will no doubt be some under-recording (but no more so than for any other Hylaeus, small Lasioglossum etc.). Map gives strong evidence for a significant UK decline and there is no evidence of it increasing. Hard to find now.","1","Disagree"
