"Lasioglossum laticeps: iso. Amiet et al: 2001","212","NT?","Steven Falk","","Distribution (including specific locations), habitat requirements and general status very similar to L. angusticeps i.e. both are very restricted bees of clay-rich coastal landslips in a small part of Dorset & IOW but angusticeps is graded NT and has a different narrative to laticeps that exagerates the differences between the two. Both are vulnerable to climatic extremes, storm damage, cliff collapses etc. Narrative for laticeps states ""Edge of range taxon, thought to be limited by warmth"". I agree, but that is also the case with L. angusticeps and several other species here, and should not need to influence the national status. L. laticeps and angusticeps should be afforded the same grades unless there is good evidence for a signifiant difference in their circumstances. Both require targeted surveying and both will be impacted by irregular monitoring.","1","Undergraded?"
