"Megachile circumcincta: iso. Perkins: 1925","212","NT","Steven Falk","","No data sheet provided. Pretty frequent on dunes of the west and north (and possibly still under-recorded in Scotland) where it is usually the commonest leafcutter. I've encountered a number of strong populations in recent years, most recently in Teesside brownfield areas where it seems to be the commonest leafcutter. I agree that it needs an IUCN status but VU seems overcooked. Much more widespread than Colletes floralis (which has similar requirements).","1","Overgraded"
