"Rhopalum gracile: iso. Richards: 1980","212","VU","Steven Falk","","Insufficient data invoked as reason for DD. Surprised by this as it taxonomically stable, long-known in Britain, with a well-known distribution based on a very well-recognised habitat. A rare wasp of large, old eastern reed beds (which get a fair bit of surveying as many are SSSIs or NNRs) but the wasp seems to be much rarer than the broad habitat. Similar habitat and distribution to Odynerus simillimus which is graded VU.","1","Disagree"
