"Sphecodes ferruginatus: iso. Amiet et al: 1999","212","LC","Steven Falk","","Narrative states ""Significant ID problems, even with modern keys. May be more frequent in the midlands than the south. Noticeably scarce, though occupies a large range"". First statement is incorrect. Many Sphecodes species are somewhat challenging to identify, but N. ferruginata does not stand out as any more difficult than most of the others and males are particularly straightforward to ID using genitalia (as is necessary with most male Sphecodes not just this species). I state that as somebody who has produded a lot of online resources for this genus e.g. https://www.flickr.com/photos/63075200@N07/collections/72157638184988454/ and https://bwars.com/sites/default/files/diary_downloads/SPHECODES%20IDENTIFICATION%20WORKSHOP%20BWARS%2013%20Nov%202019_SFalk.pdf. Map and personal data suggests widespread and LC.","1","Disagree"
