"Tapinoma subboreale: iso. Seifert: 2012","212","","Paddy Saunders","","Not sure should be list as DD. Not ant expert, consult more ant experts. but even as senso.lato highly fragmented, tetrad value is 16 supports D2 ???. Subboreale only found on one population is UK, Godlingstone Heath extensive surveys for hymettus in 2011 (by me !) couldn't find at any other sites nearby (NOTE- got some vouchers determined by seifert, and name change just after I finish report so referred to as ambiguum). Not sure if more recent work by others. But agree difficult and happy to defer to Ant Experts","1","CHECK"
