"Andrena lapponica: iso. Perkins: 1919","212","LC","Liam Olds","","It is probably under-recorded in parts of the north and west, but I get the impression that it is doing well here (I frequently encounter it in suitable habitat in Wales, and I assume that will be the case in northern England and Scotland also). I don't feel that there is enough evidence of decline to warrant NT. ","1","N"
