"Bombus monticola: iso. Cameron et al: 2007","212","LC","Liam Olds","","Unclear how this species is NT when species such as B. muscorum and B. soroeensis have come out as LC. While it has declined in the south east, it is still widespread in the north and west so perhaps LC is more appropriate?  It is worth mentioning, however, that I have witenssed an apparent decline in the uplands of S. Wales over the past 7-8 years - I am finding it harder to find the species at sites where it was more abundance a few years previously (perhaps linked to increasing droughts?) but I'm not sure if this is the case elsewhere (e.g. SW England).   ","1","N"
"Bombus muscorum: iso. Cameron et al: 2007","212","NT","Liam Olds","","A species that is vulnerable to climate change and has experienced historic declines. NT may be more appropriate. ","1","N"
