"Bombus rupestris: iso. Cameron et al: 2007","212","","Liam Olds","","","0","Y"
"Bombus soroeensis: iso. Cameron et al: 2007","212","NT","Liam Olds","","I feel that is should be at least NT as it appears to be genuinely rare in England and Wales (and where it does occur it seems to be very localised) but perhaps the Scottish records are obscuring the national trend? Some of its associated habitats in England and Wales may also be threateneded (e.g. to agricultural intensification, development). Worth noting that I have searched good quality habitat across South Wales over the past 10 years and have not found it; where it was recently find by BBCT in Port Talbot, this site has since been partly lost to development. A search of quality brownfield sites nearby in 2024 (e.g. TATA Steel) has failed to relocate it. ","1","N"
