"Nomada argentata: iso. Amiet et al: 2007","212","NT","Liam Olds","","Appears to be generally scarce and its associated habitats - at least in Wales - are vulnerable to drainage (in marshy grasslands), overgrazing (removing flowers of host), development (lots of development of marshy grasslands along Heads of the Valleys for instance) etc. ","1","N"
"Nomada armata: iso. Perkins: 1919","212","NT","Liam Olds","","Restricted distribution, known often low population sizes and low dispersal ability makes it vulnerable. Poorly timed grazing removing scabious flowers is a threat, as is an absense of grazing eliminating scabious plants (I've seent his on Wiltshire Wildlife Trust sites). ","1","N"
